<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1409,2022]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,1409,1433]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[274,496,1409,1432]" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Alterosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polyacinata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[274,496,1409,1432]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Alterosa polyacinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[503,589,1409,1433]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[503,589,1409,1433]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Blahnik 2005" authorityName="Blahnik" authorityYear="2005" box="[728,1131,1409,1432]" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Alterosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caparaonensis">
<emphasis box="[728,979,1409,1432]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Alterosa caparaonensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Blahnik" box="[987,1131,1409,1432]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" refString="Blahnik, R. J. (2005) Alterosa, a new caddisfly genus from Brazil (Trichoptera: Philopotamidae). Zootaxa, 991, 1 - 60." type="journal article" year="2005">
Blahnik 
<number box="[1078,1131,1409,1432]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Dumas &amp; Nessimian 2013" authorityName="Dumas &amp; Nessimian" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Alterosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruschii">
<emphasis box="[1183,1353,1409,1432]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Alterosa ruschii</emphasis>
Dumas &amp; Nessimian 
<number box="[304,360,1444,1467]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</taxonomicName>
, resembling these species in having highly modified, basally branched intermediates appendages, each heavily armed with coarse setae. Additionally, the basolateral projection on tergum X and the structure and lack of spines in the phallus are also similar. The new species can be distinguished from the others by the presence of a triangular dorsal projection on tergum X and by the structure of the mesal branches of the intermediate appendages, which are divided into superior and inferior arms, whereas in 
<taxonomicName box="[698,880,1583,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Alterosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caparoenensis">
<emphasis box="[698,880,1583,1606]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">A. caparoenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in 
<taxonomicName box="[960,1064,1583,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Alterosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruschii">
<emphasis box="[960,1064,1583,1606]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">A. ruschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are not divided.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="598" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1409,2022]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1617,1641]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[348,475,1618,1641]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Adult male.</emphasis>
Length of each forewing 
<quantity box="[768,853,1618,1641]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
(n= 
<number box="[906,916,1618,1641]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="1.0">1</number>
). Color (in alcohol) brownish; legs, palps, and antennae pale brown, wings brownish-yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1409,2022]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,152,871]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="598" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis box="[151,313,1687,1710]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Tergum VIII with posteromesal margin slightly emarginate. Sternum IX with anterolateral margin strongly rounded, extending from dorsum; posteroventral margin greatly produced, forming broad expansion, subtruncate at apex (
<figureCitation box="[374,435,1756,1779]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[241,1330,200,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[233,1334,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Alterosa polyacinata sp. nov., male genitalia. A, segments IX and X and their appendages, left lateral; B, intermediate and lateral appendages (setae omitted), left lateral; C, tergum X, left lateral; D, segments IX and X and their appendages, dorsal (setae of left intermediate appendage omitted); E, left inferior appendage, ventral; F, phallus, dorsal; G, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: inf. app. — inferior appendage; int. app. — intermediate appendage; pr. app. — preanal appendage; phb—phallobase; entc—endotheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232888/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
Fig. 
<number box="[425,435,1756,1779]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Tergum IX fused to base of tergum X. Tergum X, in dorsal view, broad at base, abruptly narrowed at apical second third; with mesal projection over base of tergum (
<figureCitation box="[968,1028,1791,1814]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[241,1330,200,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[233,1334,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Alterosa polyacinata sp. nov., male genitalia. A, segments IX and X and their appendages, left lateral; B, intermediate and lateral appendages (setae omitted), left lateral; C, tergum X, left lateral; D, segments IX and X and their appendages, dorsal (setae of left intermediate appendage omitted); E, left inferior appendage, ventral; F, phallus, dorsal; G, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: inf. app. — inferior appendage; int. app. — intermediate appendage; pr. app. — preanal appendage; phb—phallobase; entc—endotheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232888/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
Fig. 
<number box="[1018,1028,1791,1814]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D); projection triangular and broadest apically, with seven irregular stout spines, five apically and two subapically positioned, and one tiny apicomesal spine (
<figureCitation box="[159,230,1860,1883]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[241,1330,200,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[233,1334,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Alterosa polyacinata sp. nov., male genitalia. A, segments IX and X and their appendages, left lateral; B, intermediate and lateral appendages (setae omitted), left lateral; C, tergum X, left lateral; D, segments IX and X and their appendages, dorsal (setae of left intermediate appendage omitted); E, left inferior appendage, ventral; F, phallus, dorsal; G, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: inf. app. — inferior appendage; int. app. — intermediate appendage; pr. app. — preanal appendage; phb—phallobase; entc—endotheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232888/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
Figs. 
<number box="[220,230,1860,1883]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C, 
<number box="[267,277,1860,1883]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="1.0">1</number>
D); basolaterally with scrabous cuticle broadly projecting ventrolaterad, bearing numerous long spine-like setae ventrolaterally (
<figureCitation box="[380,440,1895,1918]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[241,1330,200,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[233,1334,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Alterosa polyacinata sp. nov., male genitalia. A, segments IX and X and their appendages, left lateral; B, intermediate and lateral appendages (setae omitted), left lateral; C, tergum X, left lateral; D, segments IX and X and their appendages, dorsal (setae of left intermediate appendage omitted); E, left inferior appendage, ventral; F, phallus, dorsal; G, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: inf. app. — inferior appendage; int. app. — intermediate appendage; pr. app. — preanal appendage; phb—phallobase; entc—endotheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232888/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
Fig. 
<number box="[430,440,1895,1918]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C); apex sensillate, rounded, moderately enlarged in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1142,1212,1895,1918]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[241,1330,200,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[233,1334,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Alterosa polyacinata sp. nov., male genitalia. A, segments IX and X and their appendages, left lateral; B, intermediate and lateral appendages (setae omitted), left lateral; C, tergum X, left lateral; D, segments IX and X and their appendages, dorsal (setae of left intermediate appendage omitted); E, left inferior appendage, ventral; F, phallus, dorsal; G, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: inf. app. — inferior appendage; int. app. — intermediate appendage; pr. app. — preanal appendage; phb—phallobase; entc—endotheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232888/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
Figs. 
<number box="[1202,1212,1895,1918]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[1248,1258,1895,1918]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="1.0">1</number>
C). Intermediate appendages sclerotized, paired, moderately elongate, length subequal to preanal appendages, branched basally (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1406,1930,1953]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[241,1330,200,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[233,1334,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Alterosa polyacinata sp. nov., male genitalia. A, segments IX and X and their appendages, left lateral; B, intermediate and lateral appendages (setae omitted), left lateral; C, tergum X, left lateral; D, segments IX and X and their appendages, dorsal (setae of left intermediate appendage omitted); E, left inferior appendage, ventral; F, phallus, dorsal; G, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: inf. app. — inferior appendage; int. app. — intermediate appendage; pr. app. — preanal appendage; phb—phallobase; entc—endotheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232888/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">
Figs. 
<number box="[1396,1406,1930,1953]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[151,162,1964,1987]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" value="1.0">1</number>
B), both mesal and lateral branches of appendages covered with coarse setae; mesal branches each forked subbasally, its superior arm finger-like, slightly curved outward as viewed dorsally, its inferior arm capitate; lateral branches clavate (
<figureCitation box="[159,231,152,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[241,1330,200,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[233,1334,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Alterosa polyacinata sp. nov., male genitalia. A, segments IX and X and their appendages, left lateral; B, intermediate and lateral appendages (setae omitted), left lateral; C, tergum X, left lateral; D, segments IX and X and their appendages, dorsal (setae of left intermediate appendage omitted); E, left inferior appendage, ventral; F, phallus, dorsal; G, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: inf. app. — inferior appendage; int. app. — intermediate appendage; pr. app. — preanal appendage; phb—phallobase; entc—endotheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232888/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="598">
Figs. 
<number box="[221,231,152,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="598" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[270,281,152,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="598" value="1.0">1</number>
B,). Preanal appendages setose, slender, moderately elongate, not greatly modified, slightly enlarged near mid length; apex with few short, spine-like setae (
<figureCitation box="[680,749,186,209]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[241,1330,200,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[233,1334,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Alterosa polyacinata sp. nov., male genitalia. A, segments IX and X and their appendages, left lateral; B, intermediate and lateral appendages (setae omitted), left lateral; C, tergum X, left lateral; D, segments IX and X and their appendages, dorsal (setae of left intermediate appendage omitted); E, left inferior appendage, ventral; F, phallus, dorsal; G, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: inf. app. — inferior appendage; int. app. — intermediate appendage; pr. app. — preanal appendage; phb—phallobase; entc—endotheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232888/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="598">
Figs. 
<number box="[739,749,186,209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="598" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[785,796,186,209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="598" value="1.0">1</number>
B). Inferior appendages setose, elongate, linear, flattened on mesal surface (
<figureCitation box="[314,386,224,247]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[241,1330,200,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[233,1334,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Alterosa polyacinata sp. nov., male genitalia. A, segments IX and X and their appendages, left lateral; B, intermediate and lateral appendages (setae omitted), left lateral; C, tergum X, left lateral; D, segments IX and X and their appendages, dorsal (setae of left intermediate appendage omitted); E, left inferior appendage, ventral; F, phallus, dorsal; G, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: inf. app. — inferior appendage; int. app. — intermediate appendage; pr. app. — preanal appendage; phb—phallobase; entc—endotheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232888/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="598">
Figs. 
<number box="[376,386,224,247]" pageId="2" pageNumber="598" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[424,434,224,247]" pageId="2" pageNumber="598" value="1.0">1</number>
E); first article, in lateral view, narrow, about three times longer than wide, slightly larger at base; second article shorter than first, its apex rounded, slightly enlarged with small pad of short, stiff apicomesal setae (
<figureCitation box="[159,230,293,316]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[241,1330,200,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[233,1334,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Alterosa polyacinata sp. nov., male genitalia. A, segments IX and X and their appendages, left lateral; B, intermediate and lateral appendages (setae omitted), left lateral; C, tergum X, left lateral; D, segments IX and X and their appendages, dorsal (setae of left intermediate appendage omitted); E, left inferior appendage, ventral; F, phallus, dorsal; G, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: inf. app. — inferior appendage; int. app. — intermediate appendage; pr. app. — preanal appendage; phb—phallobase; entc—endotheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232888/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="598">
Figs. 
<number box="[220,230,293,316]" pageId="2" pageNumber="598" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[268,278,293,316]" pageId="2" pageNumber="598" value="1.0">1</number>
E). Phallobase tubular, elongate, narrow, weakly curved at midlength; endotheca without evident spines or phallotremal sclerites (
<figureCitation box="[394,464,328,351]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[241,1330,200,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[233,1334,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Alterosa polyacinata sp. nov., male genitalia. A, segments IX and X and their appendages, left lateral; B, intermediate and lateral appendages (setae omitted), left lateral; C, tergum X, left lateral; D, segments IX and X and their appendages, dorsal (setae of left intermediate appendage omitted); E, left inferior appendage, ventral; F, phallus, dorsal; G, phallus, left lateral. Abbreviations: inf. app. — inferior appendage; int. app. — intermediate appendage; pr. app. — preanal appendage; phb—phallobase; entc—endotheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232888/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="598">
Figs. 
<number box="[454,464,328,351]" pageId="2" pageNumber="598" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F, 
<number box="[494,504,328,351]" pageId="2" pageNumber="598" value="1.0">1</number>
G).
</paragraph>
